7. MIGRATION ORDER (phased DAG)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Phase 0 — Types + read path (no behavior change)
  Depends: —
  - Define PolityMacroState + Default row from existing faction_treasury/resources
  - Add WorldState.polities: BTreeMap<u32, PolityMacroState> #[serde(default)]
  - On load/new sim: hydrate polities from factions+treaury+resources HashMaps
  - Simulation accessors; tests assert hydration parity

Phase 1 — Per-polity unrest/belief/cohesion (highest leverage)
  Depends: Phase 0
  - Add phase_polity_mood or split phase_unrest/phase_cohesion to write per-row
  - Drive each row from: row treasury/resources, local population (count ECS
    Alignment::Faction(id)), faction-local food stress; optional bleed from
    global market_state.prices("food") until per-polity markets exist
  - phase_diplomacy: replace self.belief()/cohesion()/unrest() with
    (polity[a].belief + polity[b].belief)/2 or max-pairwise — document choice
  - Dual-write: update globals as mean/max of polity rows for HUD backward compat
  - Tests: diplomacy_faction_pair tests (~L4540+) with divergent per-polity unrest

Phase 2 — Per-polity institutions + stratification
  Depends: Phase 1
  - temple_level, garrison_level, dispossessed_permille per row
  - phase_institutions: per-polity upkeep from own treasury (remove keys().min hack)
  - inequality_unrest: compute spread against peer treasuries in pair diplomacy

Phase 3 — Per-polity research/tech/focus (expensive coupling)
  Depends: Phase 2
  - research_progress, tech_unlocks, economic_focus per row
  - phase_research/phase_tech/phase_economic_focus iterate polities BTreeMap order
  - chronicle: tag entries with PolityId

Phase 4 — Shadow scalars (CIV-0105 substrate, no graph yet)
  Depends: Phase 1 (legitimacy couples to unrest/cohesion)
  - Add legitimacy_milli, shadow_influence_index_milli, influence_capital,
    governance_integrity_milli to PolityMacroState
  - New phase_shadow or subsection of phase_institutions: integer milli updates,
    audit log vec per tick (replay bus) — no silent application
  - Wire diplomacy_conflict_threshold bias from shadow_influence peer differential

Phase 5 — Pairwise diplomacy unification
  Depends: Phase 1
  - Route faction_relations through civ_diplomacy::DiplomacyState (i32 standing)
  - Deprecate civ_agents::DiplomacyMatrix float scores in WorldState
  - Keep ClusterId matrix only for emergent cluster diplomacy (agents crate)

Phase 6 — Deprecate globals + fold HashMaps
  Depends: Phases 1–4 stable; HUD/RPC consumers updated
  - Remove WorldState.belief/unrest/cohesion/… globals (serde alias migration)
  - Remove faction_treasury, faction_resources, factions HashMaps — name lives
    in PolityMacroState; polities is sole registry
  - protocol_3d FactionStateFrame carries shadow fields

Phase 7 (optional) — Dense SoA cache
  Depends: Phase 6 + profiling
  - Build Vec<PolityMacroState> snapshot sorted by id each tick for hot loops
  - Align faction_doctrines indexing with PolityRegistry

Parallel safe: Phase 5 can start after Phase 1; Phase 4 can overlap Phase 2.
Do NOT start Phase 6 until dual-write tests green for ≥1 milestone.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8. ANTI-PATTERNS / RISKS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  - HashMap iteration in tick phases without sort → replay drift
  - Parallel scalar HashMaps → key-set drift in saves
  - Reusing ClusterId(u64::from(faction_id)) as long-term polity identity —
    emergent clusters and registered factions will diverge; PolityId must be
    authoritative in WorldState, ClusterId in agents/emergence only
  - Float shadow scalars — CIV-0105 and civ-diplomacy use integer milli; keep
  - Applying shadow influence without audit events (violates FR-CIV-DIPLO-003)
  - Big-bang rewrite of phase_* before dual-write — breaks saves and HUD

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9. SUMMARY
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

RECOMMENDED: BTreeMap<u32, PolityMacroState> (single struct map, sorted keys).

REJECT: Parallel HashMaps per scalar (determinism + serde hazard).
DEFER: SoA Vec indexing until polity count and profiling justify it.

FIRST IMPLEMENTATION SLICE: Phase 0 + Phase 1 — hydrate map, per-polity
unrest/belief/cohesion, feed phase_diplomacy thresholds from pair-local macro
state while dual-writing globals for compatibility.
